      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for the paper **\"Large Language Models Struggle to Learn Long-Tail Knowledge\"** by Nikhil Kandpal et al., published at ICML 2023:\n\n## Paper Overview\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper is authored by **Nikhil Kandpal, Haikang Deng, Adam Roberts, Eric Wallace, and Colin Raffel**, and was published in PMLR 202, 2023"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " (Proceedings of the 40th International Conference on Machine Learning). "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It appears in ICML 2023, pages 15696–15707."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Key Findings\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper studies the relationship between the knowledge memorized by large language models and the information in pre-training datasets scraped from the web. In particular, it shows that a language model's ability to answer a fact-based question relates to how many documents associated with that question were seen during pre-training."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors identify relevant documents by entity linking pre-training datasets and counting documents that contain the same entities as a given question-answer pair."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Language models struggle to capture the long-tail of information on the web. The authors plot accuracy for the BLOOM model family on TriviaQA as a function of how many documents in the model's pre-training data are relevant to each question."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Retrieval-augmentation can reduce the dependence on relevant pre-training information, presenting a promising approach for capturing the long-tail."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## Links\n\n- **arXiv**: [https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.08411](https://arxiv.org/abs/2211.08411)\n- **ICML Proceedings**: [https://proceedings.mlr.press/v202/kandpal23a/kandpal23a.pdf](https://proceedings.mlr.press/v202/kandpal23a/kandpal23a.pdf)\n- **ACM Digital Library**: [https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.5555/3618408.3619049](https://dl.acm.org/doi/10.5555/3618408.3619049)\n- **Semantic Scholar**: [https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/75f7e9e2b59fb640ef9d1dff94097175daf46c4d](https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/75f7e9e2b59fb640ef9d1dff94097175daf46c4d)\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper was first posted on arXiv on November 15, 2022, with a revised version (v2) on July 27, 2023."
      }
